Key Match Events: Daniel Gafford exploded for 22 points and 7 rebounds in just 18 minutes off the bench.
Zach Collins put up a respectable line of 20 points and 6 rebounds, being much more effective inside than from deep.
Stephon Castle showed some of the things that indicate he will be a highly effective player for years to come, particularly his ability to use his body and strength to seal off angles for himself.
Pre-Game Insights: Acquiring more offensive creation should be a focal point for the Spurs as they continue to build the roster.
The 2025 NBA Draft class features some tantalizing offensive creators to keep an eye on.
Acquiring a big name via trade or free agency would help tremendously.
Post-Match Reflections: The Mavericks dominated the Spurs on the interior, especially Daniel Gafford.
It wasn’t the best night for Stephon Castle, but he still showed some of the things that indicate he will be a highly effective player for years to come.
Tre Jones’s first game back from injury wasn’t one to hang his hat on, but he should be a big help once the cavalry arrives.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The paint just wasn’t protected like it normally is with Wembanyama (duh).
Those back-to-back airballs will likely earn Zach Collins a spot on Shaqtin a Fool.
